Motorists who violated the curfew order in Lagos state last night, were forced to sleep at Osborne Road in Ikoyi area of the state. The federal government declared a nationwide curfew of 8pm to 6am, as part of new measures to contain the spread of the COVID-19. An Instagram user @Femiolasebikan who was among those stuck at the spot last night, wrote; “Make una help us beg Governor @jidesanwoolu oooo. We won’t do it again.. I want to go home.We’re all sleeping on the road tonight” Motorists spend the night at Osborne Road in Ikoyi, for violating the curfew order in Lagos A post shared by  Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) on May 19, 2020 at 11:03pm PDT Source Badagry (Lagos State) - The Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC), on Monday restated its advise for motorists to desist from embarking on night journeys. Mr Nseobong Akpabio, Zonal Commander, FRSC, Lagos and Ogun State, gave the advice when he viwited their office in Badagry. He said that 80 per cent… January 12, 2016 In "News" By Folasade Adeniran Lagos - The Lagos State Government said on Friday that it was investigating two Lagos State Traffic Management Authority (LASTMA) officers accused of extortion in the Ikoyi area of the state. The Deputy Governor of the state, Dr Obafemi Hamzat, made the disclosure while briefing newsmen at… June 22, 2019 In "News" By Sandra Umeh Lagos, - A Federal High Court in Lagos on Thursday issued a bench warrant for the arrest and production in court of a former Director-General of the National Intelligence Agency (NIA), Amb. Ayo Oke, and his wife, Folashade, charged with 205 million dollars concealment. The accused were… February 7, 2019 In "News"